# React Frontend Development Rules

## Tech Stack
- React 18 with TypeScript
- Vite for build tooling
- Tailwind CSS for styling
- React Router for navigation

## Component Guidelines
- Use functional components with TypeScript
- Prefer named exports over default exports
- Use descriptive component names with PascalCase
- Place components in `frontend/src/components/`
- Use TypeScript interfaces for props

## Styling Rules
- Use Tailwind CSS utility classes
- Follow mobile-first responsive design
- Use consistent spacing and color schemes
- Avoid custom CSS unless absolutely necessary

## File Organization
- Components: `frontend/src/components/`
- Utilities: `frontend/src/lib/`
- Types: Define interfaces in component files or separate type files
- API calls: Use `frontend/src/lib/api.ts`

